com.preemptive.annotation.instrumentation

Enum InjectionPoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<InjectionPoint>
      • com.preemptive.annotation.instrumentation.InjectionPoint
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<InjectionPoint>

    public enum InjectionPoint
extends java.lang.Enum<InjectionPoint>
    The location in a method where a particular instrumentation will be made. Note that BeginningAndEnd may not be valid for some types of instrumentation.

      • Beginning

        public static final InjectionPoint Beginning
        Instrumentation will be inserted at the beginning of the method.

      • End

        public static final InjectionPoint End
        Instrumentation will be inserted at the end of the method : i.e. all exit points.

      • BeginningAndEnd

        public static final InjectionPoint BeginningAndEnd
        Instrumentation will be inserted at the beginning of the method and at all exit points. If the attribute does not support this value, then it is ignored and the instrumentation uses its default value.
